{
  "content": "- **Macrophage-derived delta-like protein 1 (DLK1) enhances matrix metalloproteinase (MMP) and IL-6 production by fibroblast-like synoviocytes (FLS):** In a study by Sekine et al., it was shown that DLK1 from macrophages can stimulate FLS to produce IL-6 and MMP-3. These proteins are crucial in the degradation of the extracellular matrix and contribute to joint erosion in rheumatoid arthritis [Sekine et al., 2014]. \n\n- **Mechanisms of bone loss due to autoimmune conditions and irradiation:** Recent preprints suggest that disruptions in bone microenvironment due to immune challenges, like autoimmune diseases or irradiation, can severely affect bone mineral density and architecture. However, the exact molecular mechanisms behind these changes remain partially understood [bioRxiv, \"Disrupted bone microenvironment and immune recovery\", 2025].\n\n- **Influence of dietary interventions on inflammatory bone loss:** Another preprint describes how probiotics, such as Lactobacillus acidophilus, could modulate inflammation and prevent bone density loss in inflammatory conditions, indicating potential therapeutic avenues [Bhardwaj et al., bioRxiv, 2025].",
